properties.Subdivision_Lot: UNIT B HOMES AT 2903 COMPTON ROAD
properties.Purpose: To install a new IN-GROUND POOL with spa and deck. MUST INCLUDE REQUIRED FENCING AND/OR ALARM(S). Located to the rear of a principal structure. Installation must conform to easements on parcel. Separate permits are required for any proposed electrical, plumbing, & gas/mechanical work and is not part of this Building Permit.  Specifications:  1. 15’x28’ totaling 86 pool perimeter or 420 Sq. ft. with a pool min depth of 4’ and a pool max depth of 6’. Estimated gallons 10,839 of Fusion Salt.  2. Entrance of pool is four solid concrete steps and a sun shelf at 56 Sq. ft. with a water depth of 9”. Deep end of pool will have a built-in swim out for existing at 8’ in length. Water features include two bubblers on sun shelf, and three laminar jets w/ LED.  A Pool Eye Smart Pool Alarm PE20 will be installed as well.  3. There will be an attached spa consisting of 24 Sq. ft. installed at the height of 24” with stone veneer on both sides.  4. Installing 334 Sq. ft. of 12”x24” travertine in sand as decking.  A 34’ black drainage pipe to be installed for imperious area from pool ties into ground.   5. An existing 52” Code Compliant Pool Fence Barrier with self-latching gates to outswing from pool & lock installed at 54” from ground are to be installed. Attached to entrance gates will be a Yard Guard YG03 gate/door water hazard alarm. Door chirp will be utilized. See line #50 of A&S Contract Agreement for purchase of gate alarm at time of contract sale.
